text: Laura Gauché (born 4 March 1995) is a French alpine skier. == Career == Laura Gauché competed in the women's downhill and combined at the 2018 Winter Olympics. She finished 22nd in downhill and 12th in combined. * Best Overall FIS Alpine Ski World Cup ranking: 65th during the 2017-2018 season with 94 points. * Best Downhill FIS Alpine Ski World Cup ranking: 36th during the 2017-2018 season with 26 points. * Best Super G FIS Alpine Ski World Cup ranking: 30th during the 2017-2018 season with 49 points. * Best Combined FIS Alpine Ski World Cup ranking: 25th during the 2017-2018 season with 19 points. Best result during a FIS Alpine Ski World Cup competition: 17th in Combined in Lenzerheide, Switzerland, January 26, 2018. ==Personal life== She was a student at Middle School Saint Exupery in Bourg-Saint-Maurice, France. Then, she entered at High School Jean Moulin in Albertville, France. In 2017, she obtained a two-year diploma in marketing techniques from Annecy University Institutes of Technology. ==References== == External links == Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:French female alpine skiers Category:Alpine skiers at the 2018 Winter Olympics Category:Olympic alpine skiers of France Category:Université Savoie-Mont Blanc alumni Category:People from Savoie
